<br>
<br>
Braeadan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/02 4:57:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=73.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage all but usless for PVP (At least at low levels)</span><hr size=1> Mages can be hard at low levels because you're mostly fighting twinks.  Level 20 rangers with wurmslayers and lamentations will destroy you.  Level 20 shadowknights with Axes of Lost Souls will vaporize you.  And they probably have enough resist gear that your spells, which are inefficient at low levels anyway, will never kill em.<br>
<br>
Basically it sucks to be a low level caster on an established server.<br>
<br>
Some things that can help, if you're a twink:<br>
1) SOW potions.  Lots.  I buy them in bulk, personally.  You can outrun all the twinks with their jboots.<br>
2) Resist gear.  Especially MR gear.  Get over 100 MR asap, or as much as you can afford.<br>
<br>
If you're not a twink, basically just sic your pet on people and run like hell.  High level mage PvP is a lot like that anyway.  Low MR is the only thing that should really cause you to die consistantly -- if they can't root/snare/dark you, you should be able to run like a madman and avoid getting ganked too much.<br>
<br>
Buy Crystallized Pumice as you can afford it, too.  I still use them, even at high level, simply because being able to cast Nullify Magic 5 times without spending any mana is quite handy.<br>
<br>
<br>
Simplified Mage PvP FAQ --<br>
Q: I'm attacked by a rogue, what do I do?<br>
A: Sic pet, run away.<br>
<br>
Q: I'm attacked by a wizard, what do I do?<br>
A: Sic pet, run away.<br>
<br>
Q: I'm attacked by a monk, what do I do?<br>
A: Sic pet, run away.<br>
<br>
You get the idea.<br>
<br>
Your mage will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> always</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be a challenge to do well with in PvP.  You have to play him like an assassin.  Sneak up on people, bolt them from behind a tree, kick em when they're down style of thing.<br>
<br>
If you want a PvP powerhouse, I'd suggest wizard or rogue, though wizard is easiest.<br>
<br>
If you want to avoid dying, be a bard, paladin or cleric.  These classes at high levels are just more trouble to attack than it's worth.<br>
<br>
If you want a serious challenge, be a magician or maybe a warrior or enchanter.<br>
